h":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"ķØóĶ»Ģµ©ĪÕØŚÕÅīµŖźÕæŖµ×Čµ×äÕĘ▓Õ«īµłÉÕ╣Čķ¬īĶ»üķĆÜĶ┐ćŃĆéµĀĖÕ┐āµĄüń©ŗ’╝Ü1) ķØóĶ»Ģ Q&A’╝łanswerStream µÖ«ķĆÜÕ»╣Ķ»ØĶĘ»ÕŠä’╝ēŌåÆ AI ÕÅæ [ń¼öĶ»ĢķéĆĶ»Ę] ŌåÆ ńö©µłĘµÄźÕÅŚ ŌåÆ save","type":"architecture","updatedAt":"2026-05-24T10:45:32.725Z","version":1},"mem_mplz30us_556ff676abc1":{"concepts":["mainai-project-profile","mianmiantong-skill-selection","springboot-vue-ai-interview","agentmemory-workflow","local-markdown-issues"],"content":"MainAI ????:?????/MianMianTong AI ??????,??? E:\\My_Projects\\MainAI???? mianmiantong-server,Spring Boot 3.2 + Java 17 + MyBatis-Plus + MySQL + Redis + Spring Security + JWT + Knife4j,?? AI ?????/??/???????????????/???????????;Flyway migration ????? mianmiantong-server/src/main/resources/db/migration,? application.yml ? flyway.enabled=false???? AI-Interview/web-app,Vue 3 + Vite + TypeScript + Pinia + Vue Router,? Home/Login/Interview/Questions/Practice/WrongBook/Profile/Admin/Resume/PaperTools ???;?? AI-Interview uni-app ?????? code-review Jest ????? AGENTS.md ???? markdown issue tracker:.scratch/<feature>/PRD.md ? issues/*.md;??????? CONTEXT.md ? docs/adr/,???????? CONTEXT.md ? docs/adr?????? agentmemory ???? commit-context/history?recall/remember/recap/session-history/handoff/forget;.mcp.json ? .codex/config.toml ????? shadcn MCP??????????? skills:remember/recall/session-history/recap/handoff/commit-context/commit-history ????????;springboot-patterns?springboot-security?springboot-tdd?springboot-verification?java-coding-standards?api-design?database-migrations?docker-patterns/deployment-patterns ????;frontend-patterns?ui-ux-pro-max?e2e-testing?diagnose?security-review?documentation-lookup ???????;grill-with-docs/improve-codebase-architecture ???? CONTEXT/ADR ???????????????:shadcn ???? Vue/uni-app ?? React shadcn/ui;jpa-patterns/postgres-patterns/kotlin/openai-docs/market-research/messages-ops/ecc-tools ???????","createdAt":"2026-05-26T01:44:45.843Z","files":["AGENTS.md",".mcp.json",".codex/config.toml","mianmiantong-server/pom.xml","mianmiantong-server/src/main/resources/application.yml","AI-Interview/web-app/package.json","docs/agents/issue-tracker.md","docs/agents/domain.md"],"id":"mem_mplz30us_556ff676abc1","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"MainAI ????:?????/MianMianTong AI ??????,??? E:\\My_Projects\\MainAI???? mianmiant","type":"fact","updatedAt":"2026-05-26T01:44:45.843Z","version":1},"mem_mplz4a9c_ed0d3bf50c84":{"concepts":["mainai-project-profile","mianmiantong-skill-selection","springboot-vue-ai-interview","agentmemory-workflow","local-markdown-issues"],"content":"MainAI project profile: repo E:\\My_Projects\\MainAI is MianMianTong, an AI interview preparation platform. Backend is mianmiantong-server: Spring Boot 3.2, Java 17, MyBatis-Plus, MySQL, Redis, Spring Security, JWT, Knife4j, AI providers DeepSeek/Qwen, Aliyun Document AI, Apache POI/PDFBox. Backend modules include auth, interview, questions, answers, exams, wrong book, resume analysis/export/templates, paper tools polish/AI reduce/plagiarism reduce, coding problems, announcements, admin, quotas. Flyway migrations exist under mianmiantong-server/src/main/resources/db/migration, but application.yml currently has spring.flyway.enabled=false. Web frontend is AI-Interview/web-app: Vue 3, Vite, TypeScript, Pinia, Vue Router, CodeMirror, GSAP, Three/OGL, views for Home/Login/Interview/Reports/History/Questions/Practice/WrongBook/Profile/Admin/Resume/PaperTools. AI-Interview also contains a uni-app mini-program and a code-review Jest tool. Agent docs: AGENTS.md says local markdown issue tracker under .scratch/<feature>/PRD.md and issues/*.md; docs/agents/domain.md expects root CONTEXT.md and docs/adr, but this scan found neither. Imported local agentmemory skills are commit-context, commit-history, recall, remember, recap, session-history, handoff, forget. .mcp.json and .codex/config.toml only configure shadcn MCP. Recommended skill set for this repo: memory/session skills (remember, recall, session-history, recap, handoff, commit-context, commit-history); backend skills (springboot-patterns, springboot-security, springboot-tdd, springboot-verification, java-coding-standards, api-design, database-migrations, docker-patterns, deployment-patterns); frontend skills (frontend-patterns, ui-ux-pro-max, e2e-testing, diagnose, security-review, documentation-lookup); architecture/documentation skills (grill-with-docs, improve-codebase-architecture). Lower default priority: shadcn because the app is Vue/uni-app rather than React shadcn/ui; jpa-patterns/postgres-patterns/kotlin/openai-docs/market-research/messages-ops/ecc-tools unless specifically requested.","createdAt":"2026-05-26T01:45:44.688Z","files":["AGENTS.md",".mcp.json",".codex/config.toml","mianmiantong-server/pom.xml","mianmiantong-server/src/main/resources/application.yml","AI-Interview/web-app/package.json","docs/agents/issue-tracker.md","docs/agents/domain.md"],"id":"mem_mplz4a9c_ed0d3bf50c84","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"MainAI project profile: repo E:\\My_Projects\\MainAI is MianMianTong, an AI interv","type":"fact","updatedAt":"2026-05-26T01:45:44.688Z","version":1},"mem_mplzdr4t_54b006a59ca4":{"concepts":["mainai-skill-policy","mattpocock-skills-priority","project-working-constraints","agentmemory-workflow"],"content":"Project constraint for MainAI: prioritize the mattpocock/skills skill family as the main working constraints and workflow source for this repo. When a task matches an installed Matt Pocock engineering skill such as diagnose, grill-with-docs, improve-codebase-architecture, setup-matt-pocock-skills, frontend-patterns, backend/Spring Boot/TDD/security/verification patterns, use those skills first. Treat other imported skills and generic guidance as auxiliary unless the user explicitly asks for them or the Matt Pocock skills do not cover the task.","createdAt":"2026-05-26T01:53:06.460Z","files":["AGENTS.md","docs/agents/issue-tracker.md","docs/agents/domain.md","docs/agents/triage-labels.md"],"id":"mem_mplzdr4t_54b006a59ca4","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Project constraint for MainAI: prioritize the mattpocock/skills skill family as ","type":"fact","updatedAt":"2026-05-26T01:53:06.460Z","version":1},"mem_mplzpr1e_dbd609ddbeaa":{"concepts":["ai-interview-voice-video-plan","speech-to-text-input","realtime-voice-interview","video-interview-report","mainai-architecture"],"content":"MainAI architecture decision draft: for AI mock interview voice/video, all input modes should normalize into candidate answer text plus metadata, then continue through existing InterviewService answerStream/end/report chain. Phase 1: server-side STT endpoint POST /api/interview/{sessionId}/transcriptions using SpeechToTextService abstraction, front-end MediaRecorder voice input with transcript confirmation. Phase 2: realtime voice using audio chunks and final answer commit. Phase 3: video interview with local camera preview sharing realtime voice transcription; video is not required for report generation. Reports remain based on InterviewSession.messages and existing overallScore/dimensions/feedback/coding fields. Security: explicit mic/camera permission, file size/type/duration validation, session ownership checks, rate limits, no long-term audio/video storage by default, no full transcript or secrets in logs.","createdAt":"2026-05-26T02:02:26.210Z","files":["AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/InterviewView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/composables/useInterviewStream.ts","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/controller/interview/InterviewController.java","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/service/interview/InterviewService.java","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/entity/interview/InterviewSession.java"],"id":"mem_mplzpr1e_dbd609ddbeaa","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"MainAI architecture decision draft: for AI mock interview voice/video, all input","type":"fact","updatedAt":"2026-05-26T02:02:26.210Z","version":1},"mem_mpm0kiua_694ba8173846":{"concepts":["mainai-aliyun-asr","turn-based-realtime-voice","video-interview-local-preview","claude-code-iteration-doc"],"content":"MainAI decision update for AI interview voice/video iteration: ASR provider is fixed to Alibaba Cloud Intelligent Speech Interaction. Do not implement full-duplex real-time voice calls; implement turn-based realtime voice instead, where audio can be chunked for subtitles but only the final committed transcript is submitted as one candidate answer turn. Video interview discussion will continue later; first version should use local camera preview plus microphone transcription, without default video upload or storage.","createdAt":"2026-05-26T02:26:21.921Z","files":[".scratch/ai-interview-voice-video/PRD.md",".scratch/ai-interview-voice-video/ITERATION-CLAUDE.md"],"id":"mem_mpm0kiua_694ba8173846","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"MainAI decision update for AI interview voice/video iteration: ASR provider is f","type":"fact","updatedAt":"2026-05-26T02:26:21.921Z","version":1},"mem_mpm0sagq_01429687f0a5":{"concepts":["mainai-video-no-server-retention","browser-local-video-download","video-interview-differentiation","turn-based-transcript-flow"],"content":"MainAI video interview decision: server must not retain video files. Video recording, if implemented, is browser-local only using MediaRecorder Blob, and the user may choose to download the file to their own device. The backend should not expose video upload, query, playback, delete, or storage APIs for the first video interview version. Video interview differentiation should come from interview presence UX, local self-review artifact, camera/mic preflight, turn-based transcript flow, and optional non-scored self-check guidance rather than automated visual scoring.","createdAt":"2026-05-26T02:32:24.313Z","files":[".scratch/ai-interview-voice-video/PRD.md",".scratch/ai-interview-voice-video/ITERATION-CLAUDE.md"],"id":"mem_mpm0sagq_01429687f0a5","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"MainAI video interview decision: server must not retain video files. Video recor","type":"fact","updatedAt":"2026-05-26T02:32:24.313Z","version":1},"mem_mpm1ebta_41174c9d13f6":{"concepts":["mainai-video-interview-architecture","local-video-review","same-technical-report","browser-mediarecorder","aliyun-asr-audio-only"],"content":"MainAI video interview architecture written: video interview is positioned as real scenario pressure plus local video review plus the same technical report. Tech stack: Vue 3/TypeScript/Vite frontend, getUserMedia for camera/mic, MediaRecorder for local-only video Blob and audio chunks, URL.createObjectURL for user download, Spring Boot backend only receives audio for Alibaba Cloud ASR, existing DeepSeek/Qwen LLM and InterviewService report flow remain unchanged. No server video storage or visual scoring.","createdAt":"2026-05-26T02:49:32.493Z","files":[".scratch/ai-interview-voice-video/VIDEO-INTERVIEW-ARCHITECTURE.md",".scratch/ai-interview-voice-video/ITERATION-CLAUDE.md"],"id":"mem_mpm1ebta_41174c9d13f6","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"MainAI video interview architecture written: video interview is positioned as re","type":"fact","updatedAt":"2026-05-26T02:49:32.493Z","version":1},"mem_mpmilpal_ad6dd78f1b31":{"concepts":[],"content":"Bandai Namco WeChat mini program reverse engineering project at E:\\My_Projects\\wechat-webtool. The AppID is wx1cb4557915b2b7cd. API server: crm-app-api.bandainamcoshanghai.com. CDN: cdn-crm.bandainamcoshanghai.com. The mini program uses a custom backend (not Youzan/Weimob) with 3-layer security: JWT HS256 auth, MD5 request signing, and AES-128-ECB encryption. All API bodies are encrypted. The WXAPKG file was successfully decrypted (V1MMWX format, PBKDF2 key derivation with wxid as password and 'saltiest' as salt). 212 source modules extracted to data/wxapp_src/. The key files are: config.js (contains secretKey: 5p/9OgW9F5cJc0fOs0TXYA==, publicKey: UYx3RZCZGI6qPIjmsW65BfmLQRZY2Xu6), services/sign-api.js (exports apiSign, aesEncrypt, aesDecrypt - heavily obfuscated with __TENCENT_CHAOS_VM), and vendors/crypto-js.min.js (CryptoJS library). AES encrypt/decrypt works perfectly via Node.js dynamic execution. apiSign has a NaN timestamp bug due to Date.parse() receiving an object in the VM context. Config API endpoint was successfully called with 200 response using captured headers.","createdAt":"2026-05-26T10:51:10.028Z","files":["src/core/api_client.py","src/core/capture_addon.py","src/core/api_analyzer.py","test_crypto.js","test_api_v4.js","data/wxapp_src/services/sign-api.js","data/wxapp_src/config.js"],"id":"mem_mpmilpal_ad6dd78f1b31","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Bandai Namco WeChat mini program reverse engineering project at E:\\My_Projects\\w","type":"fact","updatedAt":"2026-05-26T10:51:10.028Z","version":1},"mem_mpmimo5p_a13f48103e69":{"concepts":[],"content":"User wants Claude Code and Codex (OpenAI's coding agent) to collaborate on the Bandai Namco API reverse engineering project. The preferred strategy: both AIs work on different solution paths simultaneously, competing to reach a working solution first. \n\nProposed collaboration strategy:\n1. Handoff document at HANDOFF.md shared as common context\n2. Assign different solution paths: Path A (fix VM Date) vs Path B (reverse MD5 formula) vs Path D (pure Node.js reimplementation)\n3. Each AI independently implements their approach\n4. First to produce a working end-to-end API call (200 response from encrypted endpoint) wins\n5. Merge the best parts of both solutions\n\nClaude Code's advantages: Deep project context (hours of work), working encryption/decryption, all source code extracted, knows the WXAPKG decryption algorithm.\nCodex's advantages: Different reasoning model, might spot something missed, clean slate approach.","createdAt":"2026-05-26T10:51:55.212Z","files":["HANDOFF.md"],"id":"mem_mpmimo5p_a13f48103e69","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"User wants Claude Code and Codex (OpenAI's coding agent) to collaborate on the B","type":"workflow","updatedAt":"2026-05-26T10:51:55.212Z","version":1},"mem_mpqvchk9_1a21c1251d92":{"concepts":["MainAI","agentmemory","docx-preserve-format","DocxPatchApplier","DocxDocumentXmlPatcher","article-export"],"content":"MainAI 2026-05-29 note. agentmemory works via local CLI D:\\Development_Environ\\Nodejs\\nodejs\\node_modules\\@agentmemory\\mcp\\node_modules\\.bin\\agentmemory.cmd and MCP shim D:\\Development_Environ\\Nodejs\\nodejs\\agentmemory-mcp.cmd. Root cause of the broken setup: npx agentmemory uses the wrong package name, and the outer @agentmemory/agentmemory install lacks dependencies. The complete dependency tree is under @agentmemory/mcp/node_modules. The daemon must write ~/.agentmemory/engine-state.json and iii.pid, so sandboxed startup fails with EPERM; start it with local machine permissions. DOCX preserve-format export strategy: only patch target paragraphs. Normal body/table/header/footer paragraphs use DocxPatchApplier with POI. Text boxes and shapes use DocxDocumentXmlPatcher, which locally patches word/document.xml text nodes instead of reserializing the whole document.xml via DOM Transformer. This protects templates, fonts, images, and text box positions. Resume preserve-format export should use highlights only. Paper tools academic polish, AI-reduce, and plagiarism-reduce preserve-format export should send only changed paragraphs; standard export can still send full text.","createdAt":"2026-05-29T11:58:59.815Z","files":["mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/service/document/DocxPatchApplier.java","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/service/document/DocxDocumentXmlPatcher.java","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/service/document/TemplatePreservingExportService.java","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PolishView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/AiReduceView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PlagiarismReduceView.vue"],"id":"mem_mpqvchk9_1a21c1251d92","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"MainAI 2026-05-29 note. agentmemory works via local CLI D:\\Development_Environ\\N","type":"architecture","updatedAt":"2026-05-29T11:58:59.815Z","version":1},"mem_mprrnx4v_4cf4af20a332":{"concepts":["MainAI","paper-tools","local-knowledge-base","IndexedDB","Dexie","privacy","RAG"],"content":"Paper tools local knowledge base decision: KB must be browser-local only. Store papers/chunks/search metadata in IndexedDB via Dexie; do not persist papers, chunks, embeddings, prompts, or KB state on the server. First iteration should use local parsing + chunking + MiniSearch/FlexSearch keyword retrieval + Top-K chunk injection to backend LLM calls. Backend only receives current question/task and selected Top-K chunks, calls China-based LLM service, returns result, and must not log or persist context chunk bodies. Add optional JSON backup/restore locally; embeddings via transformers.js/Web Worker are phase 2.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T03:03:40.926Z","files":["AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PolishView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/AiReduceView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PlagiarismReduceView.vue","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/controller/paper/"],"id":"mem_mprrnx4v_4cf4af20a332","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Paper tools local knowledge base decision: KB must be browser-local only. Store ","type":"architecture","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T03:03:40.926Z","version":1},"mem_mprrs3hw_71c76e2fed8f":{"concepts":["MainAI","paper-tools","academic-research-skills","local-knowledge-base","quality-gates","citation-audit"],"content":"Reviewed Imbad0202/academic-research-skills for MainAI paper tools. It is useful as workflow/prompt architecture, not as a direct storage implementation. Adoptable ideas: corpus-first retrieval, user-owned literature corpus, data access levels raw/redacted/verified_only, material-passport-like metadata, no silent skip, claim/citation support checks, style calibration, writing quality checks, and integrity gates. Keep MainAI KB browser-local via IndexedDB; do not copy ARS full autonomous pipeline or multi-agent complexity into the product MVP.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T03:06:55.795Z","files":["AI-Interview/web-app/src/modules/paper-kb/","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/controller/paper/"],"id":"mem_mprrs3hw_71c76e2fed8f","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Reviewed Imbad0202/academic-research-skills for MainAI paper tools. It is useful","type":"architecture","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T03:06:55.795Z","version":1},"mem_mprt11j5_f258e216891e":{"concepts":["MainAI","paper-kb-demo","IndexedDB","Dexie","MiniSearch","privacy","review"],"content":"Reviewed paper local knowledge base demo on 2026-05-30. Direction is correct: frontend paper-kb module with Dexie, parser, chunker, MiniSearch retriever, backup/restore panel, and backend ContextChunk pass-through for AI reduce/plagiarism reduce. Backend compile passes. Frontend build fails partly due existing issues and partly due demo issues: paperParser pdfjs TextItem typing, paperSearchIndex MiniSearch limit option/type predicate, unused buildAugmentedQuestion/searchChunks/RetrievedChunk, and PolishView local const notes shadows ref then notes.value fails. Design gaps: use real fingerprint not title, local pdf worker instead of CDN, backend contextChunks needs max count/length validation and redaction helper, Polish should send contextChunks or use a distinct augmentedNotes variable, and UI should display retrieval hit count/references/no-silent-skip.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T03:41:52.767Z","files":["AI-Interview/web-app/src/modules/paper-kb/","AI-Interview/web-app/src/components/PaperKbPanel.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PolishView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/AiReduceView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PlagiarismReduceView.vue","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/dto/paper/ContextChunk.java","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/service/paper/AiReduceService.java","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/service/paper/PlagiarismReduceService.java"],"id":"mem_mprt11j5_f258e216891e","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Reviewed paper local knowledge base demo on 2026-05-30. Direction is correct: fr","type":"architecture","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T03:41:52.767Z","version":1},"mem_mprux37k_88bc695ca997":{"concepts":["MainAI","paper-kb-review","frontend-build","PaperContextSanitizer"],"content":"Reviewed fixed paper KB demo on 2026-05-30. Backend compile passes. Frontend build still fails; demo-specific remaining issues are paperSearchIndex returning mapped nullable array with a type predicate mismatch, unused searchChunks/RetrievedChunk imports in usePaperKnowledgeBase, and unused lastRetrievedCount/lastRetrievedPaperCount destructuring in PolishView. Previous major issues were fixed: local pdfjs worker, pdfjs item type guard, fingerprint uses file metadata, PolishView augmentedNotes no longer shadows notes ref, shared usePaperKbPanel exists, and backend PaperContextSanitizer caps context chunks and logs only count/length.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T04:34:47.550Z","files":["AI-Interview/web-app/src/modules/paper-kb/paperSearchIndex.ts","AI-Interview/web-app/src/modules/paper-kb/usePaperKnowledgeBase.ts","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PolishView.vue","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/service/paper/PaperContextSanitizer.java"],"id":"mem_mprux37k_88bc695ca997","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Reviewed fixed paper KB demo on 2026-05-30. Backend compile passes. Frontend bui","type":"fact","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T04:34:47.550Z","version":1},"mem_mprvkciq_ac7a2f8da988":{"concepts":["paper local knowledge base","privacy","frontend retrieval","backend sanitizer"],"content":"2026-05-30 continued paper local-KB optimization. Frontend usePaperKbPanel now accepts KbRetrievalHints and builds a task-aware retrieval query from focusText/sourceText/annotations/notes before representative body text, resets stale retrieval counters before each lookup, and keeps results local until only selected contextChunks are sent. Polish passes task/topic/notes into retrieval; AI-reduce passes scan flagged sentence reasons/suggestions plus topic/notes; plagiarism-reduce passes source reference/report annotations/notes. AI-reduce and plagiarism-reduce now display KB hit counts like polish. Backend PaperContextSanitizer now skips null chunks, normalizes blank titles/sections safely, keeps no-content logging, and has focused JUnit coverage for null/empty input, invalid chunks, max chunks, per-chunk length, total length, and prompt formatting. Verification: mvn -q -Dtest=PaperContextSanitizerTest test passed; mvn -q -DskipTests compile passed. npm run build still fails due existing unrelated project TS debt (unused vars, missing three types, QuotaInfo mismatch, style typing, etc.), not new paper-kb syntax.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T04:52:52.705Z","files":["AI-Interview/web-app/src/composables/usePaperKbPanel.ts","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PolishView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/AiReduceView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PlagiarismReduceView.vue","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/service/paper/PaperContextSanitizer.java","mianmiantong-server/src/test/java/com/mianmiantong/service/paper/PaperContextSanitizerTest.java"],"id":"mem_mprvkciq_ac7a2f8da988","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"2026-05-30 continued paper local-KB optimization. Frontend usePaperKbPanel now a","type":"workflow","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T04:52:52.705Z","version":1},"mem_mprw5221_f15d5cffdbbd":{"concepts":["frontend build","TypeScript","Vue","technical debt cleanup"],"content":"2026-05-30 fixed web-app npm run build TypeScript blockers with narrow, non-behavioral changes. Added optional query params to utils/request.get so existing get('/api/questions', params) calls type-check and actually serialize params. Normalized useQuota output to exported QuotaInfo with required unlimited computed from isAdmin/hasApiKey. Removed unused Vue imports/refs/state from visual components; useScrollReveal now stores the gsap.fromTo tween and kills it on unmount instead of an unassigned ScrollTrigger. Added src/types/three.d.ts and included d.ts files in tsconfig; GridScan keeps three runtime behavior while using any for unavailable Three type members. Converted paper tool inline style objects to StyleValue helpers to satisfy Vue HTMLAttributes style typing. Fixed HomeView Pinia ref-unwrapping misuse, PracticeDoView option index typing and parsing, ProfileView missing aiProvider display state, and removed unused ResumeHistory score helper. Verification: npm run build in AI-Interview/web-app passed; only Vite chunk-size warnings remain.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T05:08:58.919Z","files":["AI-Interview/web-app/src/utils/request.ts","AI-Interview/web-app/src/composables/useQuota.ts","AI-Interview/web-app/src/components/DecryptedText.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/components/GlareCard.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/components/GridScan.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/components/PixelCard.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/composables/useScrollReveal.ts","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PolishView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/AiReduceView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PlagiarismReduceView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/HomeView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PracticeDoView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/ProfileView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/ResumeHistoryView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/tsconfig.app.json","AI-Interview/web-app/src/types/three.d.ts"],"id":"mem_mprw5221_f15d5cffdbbd","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"2026-05-30 fixed web-app npm run build TypeScript blockers with narrow, non-beha","type":"workflow","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T05:08:58.919Z","version":1},"mem_mps12n6c_02a64683dfae":{"concepts":["QuotaInfo","Vue StyleValue","npm build verification"],"content":"2026-05-30 re-verified requested QuotaInfo and Vue style type fixes. useQuota exports normalized QuotaInfo with required unlimited derived from isAdmin/hasApiKey, and paper-tool pages use ref<QuotaInfo> instead of local partial quota shapes. PolishView and AiReduceView replace inline dynamic paragraph style objects with StyleValue-returning headingStyle/bodyStyle helpers and normalize textAlign to allowed values. npm run build in AI-Interview/web-app passed; only Vite chunk-size warnings remain, no QuotaInfo or style typing errors.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T07:27:04.400Z","files":["AI-Interview/web-app/src/composables/useQuota.ts","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PolishView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/AiReduceView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PlagiarismReduceView.vue"],"id":"mem_mps12n6c_02a64683dfae","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"2026-05-30 re-verified requested QuotaInfo and Vue style type fixes. useQuota ex","type":"fact","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T07:27:04.400Z","version":1},"mem_mps40cou_e238f02b2b66":{"concepts":["PDF upload","paper tools","Response.json empty body","frontend error handling"],"content":"Paper tool PDF upload bug investigation on sample C:/Users/Administrator.DESKTOP-1VT94J9/Downloads/µ¢ćńī«/Ķ»Ģķ¬ī.pdf: backend /api/paper/upload and Vite proxy both parsed the PDF successfully (fileType=pdf, paragraphCount=10, fullTextLength=6201), so the reported browser error `Failed to execute 'json' on 'Response': Unexpected end of JSON input` was caused by frontend upload code calling response.json() directly when an empty or non-JSON response is returned. Added shared frontend helper readJsonResponse in AI-Interview/web-app/src/utils/httpResponse.ts and updated PolishView, AiReduceView, and PlagiarismReduceView upload/report parsing calls to use it, producing clear fallback errors instead of raw DOM JSON parse failures. Verification passed: npm run build in AI-Interview/web-app and mvn -q -DskipTests compile in mianmiantong-server; sample PDF upload through http://localhost:5173/api/paper/upload returned valid JSON.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T08:49:16.340Z","files":["AI-Interview/web-app/src/utils/httpResponse.ts","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PolishView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/AiReduceView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PlagiarismReduceView.vue","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/controller/paper/PaperUploadController.java"],"id":"mem_mps40cou_e238f02b2b66","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Paper tool PDF upload bug investigation on sample C:/Users/Administrator.DESKTOP","type":"bug","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T08:49:16.340Z","version":1},"mem_mps4c3vz_4e581f875092":{"concepts":["PDF upload","HTTP 403","paper tools","frontend authentication","authFetch"],"content":"After fixing PDF JSON parsing, user saw `µ¢ćõ╗ČĶ¦Żµ×ÉÕż▒Ķ┤ź: µ¢ćõ╗ČõĖŖõ╝ĀÕż▒Ķ┤ź’╝łHTTP 403’╝ē`. Reproduced with curl through Vite proxy: no Authorization or empty `Bearer ` returned 403, while `Bearer dev-token-2` returned 200 for the same PDF. Root cause is authentication state/token missing or invalid, not PDF parsing. Added shared frontend `authFetch` helper that restores token from Pinia/localStorage, injects Authorization, and clears/login-redirects on 401/403 with a clear `ńÖ╗ÕĮĢńŖČµĆüÕĘ▓Õż▒µĢł’╝īĶ»ĘķćŹµ¢░ńÖ╗ÕĮĢÕÉÄÕåŹĶ»Ģ` message. Updated paper tools (PolishView, AiReduceView, PlagiarismReduceView) to use authFetch for upload, report analyze, scan, run/rewrite, and export requests so auth failures are not mislabeled as file parse failures. Verification: `npm run build` in AI-Interview/web-app passed.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T08:58:24.813Z","files":["AI-Interview/web-app/src/utils/authFetch.ts","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PolishView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/AiReduceView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PlagiarismReduceView.vue"],"id":"mem_mps4c3vz_4e581f875092","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"After fixing PDF JSON parsing, user saw `µ¢ćõ╗ČĶ¦Żµ×ÉÕż▒Ķ┤ź: µ¢ćõ╗ČõĖŖõ╝ĀÕż▒Ķ┤ź’╝łHTTP 403’╝ē`. Reproduced w","type":"bug","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T08:58:24.813Z","version":1},"mem_mps4jjep_8d425a73433c":{"concepts":["paper knowledge base","PDF parsing","pdfjs-dist","local-only privacy","Vite worker"],"content":"User clarified the real issue: knowledge base PDF import fails for C:/Users/Administrator.DESKTOP-1VT94J9/Downloads/µ¢ćńī«/Ķ»Ģķ¬ī.pdf and should be fixed without sending knowledge-base documents to the server. Diagnosed that the knowledge-base import path uses frontend-local `parsePaperFile`/pdfjs, not backend `/api/paper/upload`. The sample PDF is valid text PDF: minimal pdfjs legacy parse with disableWorker extracted 4 pages and 6271 chars, first text starts `ĶĄäµ║ÉõĖÄńÄ»Õóāń¦æÕŁ”Ķ┐øÕ▒Ģ 2022 Õ╣┤ń¼¼ 1 ÕŹĘń¼¼ 2 µ£¤...`. Fixed local parser by switching PDF parsing to `pdfjs-dist/legacy/build/pdf.mjs`, passing `Uint8Array`, setting `disableWorker: true`/`useWorkerFetch: false` to avoid Vite/browser worker resource failures, cleaning pages/pdf, normalizing whitespace, and throwing a clear error if no text is extracted. Added knowledge-base error state/display so import parse failures show inside PaperKbPanel instead of being unhandled or confused with ordinary upload/auth failures. Verified `npm run build` passes and the sample PDF parses in the minimal loop.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T09:04:11.520Z","files":["AI-Interview/web-app/src/modules/paper-kb/paperParser.ts","AI-Interview/web-app/src/composables/usePaperKbPanel.ts","AI-Interview/web-app/src/components/PaperKbPanel.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PolishView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/AiReduceView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PlagiarismReduceView.vue"],"id":"mem_mps4jjep_8d425a73433c","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"User clarified the real issue: knowledge base PDF import fails for C:/Users/Admi","type":"bug","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T09:04:11.520Z","version":1},"mem_mps4u8xr_2c353b9287c2":{"concepts":["paper export","PDF input","DOCX preserve format","OOXML validation","format preservation boundary"],"content":"Fixed paper-tools export bug where PDF documents could be sent to `/api/paper-export/preserve-format`, causing `DOCX locate failed: No valid entries or contents found, this is not a valid OOXML`. Root cause: preserve-format export is a DOCX template patcher and cannot process PDF fixed-layout files. Added backend guard in PaperExportController to reject non-.docx preserve-format requests with HTTP 400 JSON explaining that original-format/image preservation currently supports DOCX only. Added frontend `isDocxFile` utility and wired PolishView, AiReduceView, PlagiarismReduceView to hide the preserve-format export option for PDF/non-original-file cases and fall back to standard Word export if preserve is invoked programmatically. Verified `npm run build` for web app and `mvn -q -DskipTests compile` for server both pass. Note: true PDF format/image-preserving export requires a separate PDF export/overlay pipeline, not the DOCX patcher.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T09:12:31.165Z","files":["mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/controller/paper/PaperExportController.java","AI-Interview/web-app/src/utils/documentFile.ts","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PolishView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/AiReduceView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PlagiarismReduceView.vue"],"id":"mem_mps4u8xr_2c353b9287c2","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Fixed paper-tools export bug where PDF documents could be sent to `/api/paper-ex","type":"bug","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T09:12:31.165Z","version":1},"mem_mps4x4pw_809c651eb495":{"concepts":["PDF export","paper tools","format preserving export","PDFBox","overlay pipeline"],"content":"Discussed adding a dedicated PDF export chain for paper tools. Current preserve-format export is DOCX-only; PDF requires a separate fixed-layout pipeline. Recommended iterations: v1 standard PDF export from optimized text; v2 original PDF as background plus annotations/overlay summary (visual preservation); v3 true target-text replacement using PDFBox text-position extraction, redaction rectangles, font fallback, line wrapping, and confidence-based patching. The practical MVP should expose a separate `/api/paper-export/pdf-*` endpoint and never send PDF into DOCX preserve-format. Existing dependency PDFBox 3.0.3 is available.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T09:14:45.666Z","files":["mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/controller/paper/PaperExportController.java","mianmiantong-server/pom.xml"],"id":"mem_mps4x4pw_809c651eb495","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Discussed adding a dedicated PDF export chain for paper tools. Current preserve-","type":"architecture","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T09:14:45.666Z","version":1},"mem_mps54qhz_ed08d1a9ff33":{"concepts":["PDF to Word","PDF export","paper tools","DOCX preserve chain","format preservation"],"content":"Discussed alternative PDF export strategy: convert PDF to DOCX first, then reuse the existing DOCX template-preserving export chain. This is feasible as an intermediate-OOXML pipeline, but only if the converted DOCX is stored/transiently passed as the new template source and paragraph mappings are generated from the converted DOCX itself, not from the original PDF text extraction. It can preserve more layout/images than standard text export, but quality depends heavily on PDF type and converter. Text-based single-column PDFs are good candidates; scanned, multi-column, formula/table-heavy PDFs need OCR/layout reconstruction and lower confidence. Recommended architecture: PDF upload -> PDF-to-DOCX conversion -> run DocxTextLocator on converted DOCX -> AI editing on those paragraph identities -> TemplatePreservingExportService writes back -> export DOCX. Keep original PDF and converted DOCX transient, not persisted unless user explicitly downloads.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T09:20:40.485Z","files":["mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/controller/paper/PaperExportController.java","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/service/document/TemplatePreservingExportService.java"],"id":"mem_mps54qhz_ed08d1a9ff33","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Discussed alternative PDF export strategy: convert PDF to DOCX first, then reuse","type":"architecture","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T09:20:40.485Z","version":1},"mem_mps5svyx_767cc5361f73":{"concepts":["paper tools","PDF export beta","Aliyun DocumentMind","local knowledge base","hit details"],"content":"Implemented paper-tool beta PDF preserve export by converting PDF to DOCX via Aliyun DocumentMind ConvertPdfToWord, polling GetDocumentConvertResult, downloading transient DOCX, then using existing template-preserving write-back/content matching against the converted DOCX. Frontend Polish/AiReduce/PlagiarismReduce now show DOCX preserve export only for DOCX, and a separate 'PDF ĶĮ¼ Word õ┐ØńĢÖÕ»╝Õć║ Beta' action only for PDF, with standard Word fallback on failure. Knowledge-base retrieval now keeps lastRetrievedChunks and KbHitDetails displays clickable hit details plus the current optimized/result text for review. Verified with backend `mvn -q -DskipTests compile` and frontend `npm run build`.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T09:39:27.319Z","files":["AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PolishView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/AiReduceView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PlagiarismReduceView.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/components/KbHitDetails.vue","AI-Interview/web-app/src/composables/usePaperKbPanel.ts","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/controller/paper/PaperExportController.java","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/service/document/DocumentAiService.java","mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/service/document/TemplatePreservingExportService.java"],"id":"mem_mps5svyx_767cc5361f73","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Implemented paper-tool beta PDF preserve export by converting PDF to DOCX via Al","type":"workflow","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T09:39:27.319Z","version":1},"mem_mps6do5b_ed2160856f60":{"concepts":["PDF export beta","Aliyun DocumentMind","SubmitConvertPdfToWordJobAdvance","null data response"],"content":"Fixed PDF-to-Word beta error handling after Aliyun SubmitConvertPdfToWordJobAdvance returned body.data=null, causing NPE at getData().getId(). DocumentAiService now validates submit response body/data/id, logs code/message/requestId/rawBody, returns a business error instead of NPE, validates GetDocumentConvertResult body/status/code similarly, and removed the extra forceExportInnerImage request parameter to match Aliyun official Java example using only fileUrlObject and fileName. Verified with `mvn -q -DskipTests compile`.","createdAt":"2026-05-30T09:55:36.958Z","files":["mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/service/document/DocumentAiService.java"],"id":"mem_mps6do5b_ed2160856f60","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Fixed PDF-to-Word beta error handling after Aliyun SubmitConvertPdfToWordJobAdva","type":"bug","updatedAt":"2026-05-30T09:55:36.958Z","version":1},"mem_mpt7wts6_d34eaae6f608":{"concepts":["SSE","streaming","contenteditable","diff","polish","Ķ«║µ¢ćµČ”Ķē▓","token trimming"],"content":"Ķ«║µ¢ćµČ”Ķē▓ķĪĄķØóõ┐«ÕżŹ (2026-05-31)’╝ÜõĖēõĖ¬ķŚ«ķóś ŌĆö SSE token Ķó½ trim() ÕÉ×µÄēń®║µĀ╝’╝łµö╣õĖ║ JSON ÕŁŚń¼”õĖ▓õ╝ĀĶŠō’╝ēŃĆüķćŹÕżŹńé╣Õć╗ń╗ĢĶ┐ć isStreaming ķöü’╝łµ¢░Õó× isPreparingPolish ÕćåÕżćµĆüķöü’╝ēŃĆücontenteditable õĖÄ diff HTML µĘĘńö©Õ»╝Ķć┤ńé╣Õć╗ÕÉÄ diff µČłÕż▒’╝łµ¢░Õó× dirty ķøåÕÉłÕī║Õłåń£¤Õ«×ĶŠōÕģź’╝ēŃĆéµČēÕÅŖµ¢ćõ╗Č’╝ÜPolishService.java, PolishView.vueŃĆéń╗Åķ¬ī’╝ÜµĄüÕ╝Å token õĖŹĶāĮ trim’╝īSSE Ķ¦Żµ×ÉÕ║öõ╗ź event block õĖ║ÕŹĢõĮŹ’╝īµīēķÆ«ķöüķ£ĆĶ”åńø¢Õ«īµĢ┤µĄüń©ŗ’╝łÕÉ½ÕēŹńĮ«ÕćåÕżćµŁźķ¬ż’╝ē’╝īcontenteditable õĖŹķĆéÕÉłńø┤µÄźµē┐ĶĮĮÕ»ī HTML diffŃĆé","createdAt":"2026-05-31T03:26:16.516Z","files":["mianmiantong-server/src/main/java/com/mianmiantong/service/paper/PolishService.java","AI-Interview/web-app/src/views/PolishView.vue"],"id":"mem_mpt7wts6_d34eaae6f608","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Ķ«║µ¢ćµČ”Ķē▓ķĪĄķØóõ┐«ÕżŹ (2026-05-31)’╝ÜõĖēõĖ¬ķŚ«ķóś ŌĆö SSE token Ķó½ trim() ÕÉ×µÄēń®║µĀ╝’╝łµö╣õĖ║ JSON ÕŁŚń¼”õĖ▓õ╝ĀĶŠō’╝ēŃĆüķćŹÕżŹńé╣Õć╗ń╗ĢĶ┐ć isStr","type":"bug","updatedAt":"2026-05-31T03:26:16.516Z","version":1},"mem_mpt7x216_5f2e8af3efee":{"concepts":["DOCX","textbox","export","resume","ń«ĆÕÄå","µ¢ćµ£¼µĪå","µĀ╝Õ╝Åõ┐ØńĢÖ","TemplatePreservingExportService"],"content":"ń«ĆÕÄå DOCX µ¢ćµ£¼µĪåÕ»╝Õć║õ┐«ÕżŹ (2026-05-31)’╝Üµ¢ćµ£¼µĪåÕåģõĖ¬õ║║õ┐Īµü»’╝łÕ¦ōÕÉŹŃĆüµ▒éĶüīµäÅÕÉæŃĆüĶüöń│╗µ¢╣Õ╝ÅńŁē’╝ēĶó½ AI ÕÄŗń╝®µł